%20stop%20the%20Red%20Army%20from%20conquering%20Berlin%20in%201945%2C%20could%20it%20save%20Ukraine%20today%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnswering%20that%20question%20first%20requires%20defining%20%E2%80%9Cactive%20defense%2C%E2%80%9D%20one%20of%20those%20broad%20military%20terms%20that%20mean%20different%20things%20to%20different%20people.%20The%20US%20Army%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farmypubs.army.mil%2FProductMaps%2FPubForm%2FDetails.aspx%3FPUB_ID%3D1021737%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Efield%20manual%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20operational%20terms%20defines%20active%20defense%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20employment%20of%20limited%20offensive%20action%20and%20counterattacks%20to%20deny%20a%20contested%20area%20or%20position%20to%20the%20enemy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20that%20isn%E2%80%99t%20what%20Ukraine%20is%20doing%2C%20Douglas%20Nash%2C%20a%20retired%20US%20Army%20colonel%20and%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D039fbe6038de222cc954284f6632f29be16c8d3ae777377fb5d2290662e3855b%26postID%3D65cbb3c1ef49b4ccc977f26e%26postSlug%3Dukraine-military-shifts-active-defensive-failed-nazi-germany-wwii-2024-2%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FHells-Gate-Battle-Cherkassy-January-February%252Fdp%252F0965758435%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Eseveral%20books%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20German%20military%20operations%20in%20World%20War%20II%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Active%20defense%20is%20meant%20to%20be%20waged%20by%20large%20units%2C%20while%20Ukraine%20appears%20to%20conducting%20small-unit%20operations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CActive%20defense%20was%20understood%20to%20be%20generally%20applicable%20to%20divisions%2C%20corps%20and%20field%20armies%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nash%20said.%20%E2%80%9CNot%20squads%2C%20platoons%2C%20companies%20and%20battalions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20scale%20of%20these%20forces%20are%20drastically%20different.%20A%20US%20field%20army%2C%20for%20example%2C%20typically%20ranges%20upwards%20of%2090%2C000%20soldiers%20while%20a%20battalion%20has%20about%201%2C000.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENazi%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20approach%20%E2%80%93%20what%20the%20Germans%20called%20%E2%80%9Celastic%20defense%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20also%20differed%20from%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20current%20tactics.%20By%20mid-1943%2C%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20strategic%20situation%20had%20become%20ominous.%20The%20Soviets%20were%20continually%20on%20the%20attack%20after%20their%20victory%20at%20Stalingrad.%20Yet%20after%20four%20years%20of%20war%2C%20Germany%20lacked%20enough%20troops%20and%20equipment%20to%20strongly%20defend%20the%20entire%202%2C000-mile-long%20Eastern%20Front.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20Western%20Allies%20were%20preparing%20to%20land%20in%20Italy%20and%20France%2C%20which%20would%20squeeze%20Germany%20in%20a%20two-front%20war.%20Thus%2C%20the%20Wehrmacht%20had%20to%20conserve%20its%20resources.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22German%20soldiers%20evacuating%20a%20house%20in%20Kharkov%20destroyed%20by%20Russian%20artillery%20fire%2C%20circa%201943.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cbb8866fcb546d2d4f4052%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222556%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGerman%20soldiers%20evacuating%20a%20house%20in%20Kharkov%20destroyed%20by%20Russian%20artillery%20fire%2C%20circa%201943.%3Cp%3EKeystone%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20solution%20devised%20by%20German%20commanders%2C%20notably%20the%20legendary%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fbiography%2FErich-von-Manstein%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EField%20Marshal%20Erich%20von%20Manstein%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20was%20a%20mobile%20defense%20that%20would%20take%20advantage%20of%20German%20tactical%20and%20operational%20prowess%2C%20especially%20of%20the%20elite%20panzer%20(tank)%20divisions.%20In%20military%20textbooks%2C%20von%20Manstein%20is%20famous%20for%20his%20%E2%80%9Cbackhand%20blow%E2%80%9D%20concept%20of%20letting%20the%20Soviets%20advance%20into%20German-occupied%20territory%2C%20and%20then%20launching%20an%20exquisitely%20timed%20counterattack%20to%20encircle%20and%20destroy%20the%20Soviet%20spearheads.%20The%20classic%20example%20is%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globeatwar.com%2Fblog-entry%2Fmansteins-february-1943-backhand-blow%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EThird%20Battle%20of%20Kharkov%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20February%201943%2C%20when%20von%20Manstein%E2%80%99s%20unleashed%20a%20planned%20counterblow%20that%20annihilated%20Soviet%20armor%20pursuing%20the%20retreating%20Germans%20after%20Stalingrad.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20this%20was%20more%20of%20a%20strategic%20rather%20than%20a%20tactical%20concept.%20%E2%80%9CVon%20Manstein%20was%20willing%20to%20trade%20space%20for%20time%20in%20order%20to%20draw%20the%20enemy%20into%20a%20well-laid%20trap%2C%20which%20would%20be%20sprung%20once%20the%20enemy's%20forces%20entered%20the%20kill%20zone%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nash%20explained.%20%E2%80%9COnce%20that%20occurred%2C%20artillery%20and%20obstacles%20would%20be%20used%20to%20pin%20the%20enemy%20in%20place%2C%20while%20mechanized%20forces%20would%20attack%20into%20the%20neck%20of%20the%20enemy%20penetration%20to%20cut%20him%20off%20and%20destroy%20him%20piecemeal%2C%20thus%20restoring%20the%20front%20line%20to%20where%20it%20was%20before.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20type%20of%20active%20defense%20was%20usually%20conducted%20at%20the%20field%20army%20level%2C%20with%20different%20units%20designated%20to%20play%20the%20defensive%20role%20by%20holding%20the%20trap%20open%2C%20while%20other%20units%20played%20the%20maneuver%20and%20offensive%20role.%20It%20usually%20worked%2C%20but%20depended%20quite%20a%20bit%20on%20the%20quality%20of%20those%20leading%20the%20battle.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20during%20its%20summer%202023%20counteroffensive%2C%20Ukraine%20did%20attempt%20larger-scale%20mechanized%20operations%20with%20its%20new%20Western-equipped%20strike%20brigades.%20But%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Russia%20%E2%80%94%20lacked%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fofficer-shortages-affect-operations-of-russian-ukrainian-militaries-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Eadequate%20numbers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20trained%20junior%20officers%20and%20command%20staffs.%20Suffering%20heavy%20losses%20for%20minimal%20gains%2C%20Ukraine%20switched%20to%20a%20trench%20warfare%20strategy%20of%20attacks%20by%20small%20units%20to%20seize%20perhaps%20a%20few%20hundred%20yards%20at%20a%20time%20to%20stem%20heavy%20losses%20from%20anti-tank%20mines%2C%20artillery%20fire%20and%20drones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201943%2C%20von%20Manstein%E2%80%99s%20counterattack%20comprised%20around%20280%2C000%20soldiers%20and%2030%20divisions.%20For%20Ukraine%2C%20%E2%80%9Coffensives%20at%20the%20level%20of%20a%20battalion%20are%20a%20major%20rarity%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Ukrainian%20officer%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fukraine-ground-commander-says-his-troops-now-active-defence-can-still-surprise-2024-01-15%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EReuters%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20January%202024.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20fires%20with%20an%20AK-47%20during%20training%20at%20an%20undetermined%20location%20in%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20February%2002%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cbbbde94aa8ee8e84ad5c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20fires%20with%20an%20AK-47%20during%20training%20at%20an%20undetermined%20location%20in%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20February%2002%2C%202024.%3Cp%3EDiego%20Herrera%20Carcedo%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3E'Static%20defense'%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20essence%20of%20von%20Manstein-esque%20victory%20is%20maneuver%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20willingness%20to%20lose%20ground%20to%20entrap%20an%20advancing%20enemy.%20The%20most%20notable%20feature%20of%20the%20Russo-Ukraine%20war%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2Fjan%2F25%2Fhow-drones-froze-ukraine-frontlines%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Ehow%20difficult%20battlefield%20maneuver%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20become%20when%20drones%20are%20constantly%20spying%20overhead%2C%20and%20guided%20missiles%20can%20strike%20targets%20from%2050%20miles%20away.%20To%20survive%2C%20Ukrainian%20and%20Russians%20troops%20try%20to%20stay%20under%20cover%20of%20trenches%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%20And%20politically%2C%20a%20policy%20of%20ceding%20ground%20%E2%80%94%20albeit%20temporarily%20%E2%80%94%20may%20not%20appeal%20to%20Ukrainian%20leaders%20who%20wore%20down%20their%20army%20in%20brutal%20battles%20to%20keep%20cities%20such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-and-ukraine-bakhmut-battle-looks-like-stalingrad-expert-says-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EBakhmut%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20one%20looks%20at%C2%A0what%20the%20Ukrainian%20armed%20forces%20are%20doing%20on%20the%20ground%20at%20this%20moment%2C%20they%20are%20pursuing%20more%20of%20a%20static%20defense%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nash%20said.%20%E2%80%9CActive%20defense%20implies%20maneuver%2C%20and%20there%20is%20very%20little%20maneuver%20happening%20at%20the%20moment%20on%20the%20Ukrainian%20side.%20The%20Russians%20are%20attempting%20to%20use%20maneuver%2C%20but%20they%20are%20paying%20an%20extraordinarily%20high%20price%20for%20it%2C%20gaining%20very%20little%20in%20exchange%20for%20very%20high%20losses%20in%20men%20and%20material.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERussia%20has%20lost%20hundreds%20of%20tanks%20and%20vehicles%20and%20as%20many%20as%2020%2C000%20troops%20in%20its%20attempts%20to%20capture%20the%20city%20of%20Avdiivka%20in%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20east.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20Ukrainians%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20conduct%20deep%20mechanized%20offensives.%20They%20simply%20lack%20the%20means%20to%20do%20so.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Ukrainians%20learned%20the%20hard%20way%20this%20past%20summer%20that%20an%20army%20must%20have%20all%20the%20pieces%20together%20in%20order%20to%20practice%20any%20kind%20of%20maneuver%20on%20the%20modern%20battlefield%2C%20even%20active%20defense%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nash%20said.%20%E2%80%9CTanks%2C%20artillery%2C%20air%20defense%2C%20air%20superiority%2C%20counter-mine%20warfare%20tools%2C%20drones%2C%20electronic%20warfare%2C%20and%20so%20on.%C2%A0%20Even%20a%20limited%20%E2%80%98active%20defense%E2%80%99%20needs%20all%20of%20these%20elements%2C%20too.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20summer%2C%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20frontal%20assault%20with%20vehicles%20hit%20mines%20and%20were%20menaced%20by%20missiles%20fired%20from%20Russian%20helicopters.%20In%20a%20later%20effort%20to%20clear%20a%20path%20through%20the%20mines%2C%20dismounted%20troops%20were%20picked%20off%20by%20attack%20drones%20and%20artillery.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENATO%20in%20the%20late%201970s%20was%20bigger%20and%20better-armed%20than%20Ukraine%20today%2C%20when%20it%20took%20up%20the%20active%20defense%20doctrine%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20clear%20how%20well%20it%20would%20have%20worked.%20NATO%20embraced%20the%20concept%20as%20a%20response%20to%20the%20USSR%E2%80%99s%20numerically%20superior%20Warsaw%20Pact%20forces%2C%20and%20the%20devastating%20effect%20of%20modern%20weapons%20seen%20in%20the%201973%20Yom%20Kippur%20War.%20The%20idea%20was%20that%20the%20West%20would%20remain%20on%20the%20strategic%20defense%2C%20using%20firepower%2C%20guided%20missiles%20and%20local%20counterattacks%20to%20attrit%20the%20Soviets%20as%20they%20advanced%20deeper%20into%20Western%20Europe.%20This%20pleased%20neither%20the%20US%20Army%2C%20which%20has%20historically%20preferred%20to%20remain%20on%20the%20offensive%2C%20nor%20West%20Germany.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EActive%20defense%20was%20adopted%20%E2%80%9Cagainst%20West%20German%20opposition%2C%20because%20the%20Germans%20did%20not%20want%20to%20give%20up%20any%20territory%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nash%20said.%20%E2%80%9CYet%20with%20overwhelming%20Soviet%20military%20power%20arrayed%20against%20it%2C%20NATO%20%E2%80%94%20led%20primarily%20by%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20felt%20it%20had%20no%20other%20choice.%E2%80%9D%20By%20the%201980s%2C%20the%20US%20Army%20had%20switched%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnationalinterest.org%2Fblog%2Fbuzz%2Fairland-battle-armys-cold-war-plan-crush-russia-ended-crushing-iraq-27477%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EAirLand%20Battle%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20concept%2C%20which%20envisaged%20taking%20the%20initiative%20in%20offensive%20operations%20to%20defeat%20an%20enemy%20attack.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221982%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22German%20Field%20Marshal