oser%20to%20urban%20centers%2C%20it%20can%20find%20workers%20and%20distribute%20food%20more%20easily.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20Stacia%20Lewis%20stepped%20into%20the%20massive%20greenhouse%20with%2018-foot-high%20walls%20of%20romaine%20and%20butterhead%20lettuce%2C%20they%20knew%20they%20had%20to%20work%20there.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20like%20I'm%20walking%20into%20Willy%20Wonka's%20factory%20or%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20Lewis%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt%20looked%20like%20everything%20I%20had%20ever%20wanted.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20three%20years%20ago%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.edengreen.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EEden%20Green%20Technology%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Lewis%20got%20the%20job.%20They'd%20never%20considered%20a%20career%20in%20agriculture%20even%20after%20having%20grown%20up%20wandering%20through%20the%20hoop%20houses%20that%20dot%20their%20aunt's%20homestead.%20But%20Eden%20Green%2C%20which%20uses%20a%20high-tech%20system%20for%20growing%20staples%20like%20arugula%20lettuce%20and%20cooking%20greens%20like%20kale%20and%20chard%20in%20Cleburne%2C%20Texas%2C%20where%20Lewis%20was%20raised%2C%20won%20them%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stacia%20Lewis%20in%20a%20greenhouse%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cbc54094aa8ee8e84ae135%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStacia%20Lewis.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Eden%20Green%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Eden%20Green's%20aims%20is%20to%20remove%20some%20of%20the%20unpredictability%20of%20farming%20by%20doing%20it%20indoors%20in%20soaring%20greenhouses%20stacked%20with%20rows%20of%20greens.%20The%20company%20is%20also%20trying%20to%20take%20on%20another%20challenge%20many%20farms%20face%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomer-retirement-surge-spark-forever-labor-shortage-jobs-workers-2023-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DEver%2520since%2520the%2520pandemic%252C%2520American%2Cto%2520join%2520the%2520Great%2520Resignation.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efinding%20enough%20workers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20do%20that%2C%20Eden%20Green%20wants%20to%20make%20agriculture%20feel%20like%20other%20careers.%20It%20offers%20health%20insurance%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-great-place-to-work-maven-paid-parental-leave-benefits-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epaid%20leave%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20it%20recently%20introduced%20a%20401(k)%20%E2%80%94%20benefits%20not%20always%20available%20to%20traditional%20farm%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20idea%20is%20to%20pull%20in%20workers%20like%20Lewis.%20Finding%20employees%20who%20might%20not%20have%20thought%20of%20ag%20is%20important%20because%20it's%20an%20industry%20that%2C%20like%20healthcare%20or%20retail%2C%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fb.org%2Fmarket-intel%2Fh-2a-growth-slows-but-remains-strong%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efaces%20trouble%20drawing%20enough%20workers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEden%20Green's%20playbook%20involves%20going%20where%20the%20people%20are.%20Cleburne%2C%20with%20a%20population%20of%20about%2034%2C000%2C%20sits%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20sprawling%20Dallas-Fort%20Worth%20region.%20That%20means%20Eden%20Green%20can%20truck%20produce%20to%20nearby%20grocery%20distribution%20centers%20and%20operate%20in%20an%20area%20with%20a%20large%20enough%20population%20to%20attract%20job%20candidates.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt's%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20traditional%20US%20farms%2C%20which%20on%20average%20span%20hundreds%20of%20acres%20in%20rural%20areas%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ers.usda.gov%2Fdata-products%2Fag-and-food-statistics-charting-the-essentials%2Ffarming-and-farm-income%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efewer%20than%20one%20in%20four%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20solving%20the%20distribution%20problem%2C%20we've%20actually%20solved%20the%20labor%20problem%2C%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20Eddy%20Badrina%2C%20the%20company's%20CEO%2C%20told%20BI.%20It's%20a%20location%20that's%20already%20a%20draw%20for%20workers.%20There's%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-increased-distribution-center-productivity-13-percent-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EWalmart%20distribution%20facility%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20less%20than%20half%20a%20mile%20down%20the%20road%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0that%20Eden%20Green%20also%20supplies%20its%20produce%20to%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-facebook-microsoft-exec-says-amazon-warehouse-job-cured-burnout-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmazon%20warehouse%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%2010%20miles%20away%2C%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20could%20work%20with%20plants%20and%20work%20in%20something%20that%20is%2C%20you%20know%2C%20environmentally%20and%20economically%20sustainable%2C%20and%20it's%20feeding%20your%20local%20community%2C%20or%20you%20could%20work%20at%20an%20Amazon%20warehouse%2C%20what%20would%20you%20do%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20one%20isn't%20necessarily%20better%20than%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Lewis%2C%2024%2C%20came%20across%20the%20job%20listing%20for%20an%20entry-level%20role%20on%20Eden%20Green's%20production%20team%2C%20they%20were%20managing%20a%20Starbucks.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20really%20wanted%20something%20more.%20I%20wanted%20to%20feel%20like%20I%20was%20doing%20something%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20facility%20of%20nearly%2083%2C000%20square%20feet%2C%20Eden%20Green%20does%20its%20growing%20without%20soil%2C%20a%20process%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbowery-farms-indoor-farm-grows-365-days-a-year-less-water-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehydroponics%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Eden%20Green%20said%20it%20uses%2098%25%20less%20water%20and%2099%25%20less%20land%20than%20traditional%20farming.%20The%20company%20is%20adding%20greenhouses%20in%20Cleburne%20that%20will%20triple%20its%20growing%20capacity.%20In%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%20it%20plans%20to%20build%2020%20greenhouses%20across%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20of%20producing%20basics%20like%20lettuce%20in%20a%20different%20way%20appealed%20to%20Lewis%2C%20who'd%20long%20been%20interested%20in%20environmental%20sustainability%20but%20wasn't%20sure%20how%20to%20make%20that%20fit%20with%20their%20job.%20Lewis%2C%20who's%20also%20a%20writer%2C%20tried%20college%20for%20a%20while%2C%20but%20they%20said%20it%20didn't%20feel%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Lewis%20has%20moved%20up%20and%20currently%20holds%20the%20job%20of%20grower.%20They%20spend%20about%20half%20their%20time%20at%20a%20computer%20placing%20orders%2C%20monitoring%20some%20of%20the%20systems%20used%20to%20run%20the%20greenhouses%2C%20and%20communicating%20with%20vendors.%20The%20predictability%20of%20the%20work%20is%20part%20of%20the%20appeal%20for%20Lewis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20still%20have%20that%20agriculture%20job%20and%20have%20a%20full-time%2C%20steady%20position%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEden%20Green%20has%2013%20harvests%20a%20year%2C%20so%20there%20aren't%20the%20ups%20and%20downs%20for%20demand%20in%20labor%20as%20is%20often%20the%20case%20with%20traditional%20growing%20methods%2C%20Badrina%20said.%20That%20changes%20the%20foundational%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsome-farmers-working-at-night-to-avoid-extreme-heat-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eassumptions%20of%20agriculture%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20workers%20have%20to%20%26quot%3Bbe%20in%20there%20every%20single%20day%20to%20plant%2C%20to%20tend%2C%20to%20harvest%2C%20to%20pack%2C%26quot%3B%20Badrina%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Eddy%20Badrina%20stands%20in%20an%20Eden%20Green%20warehouse%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cbc58ef533b039a8832eae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEddy%20Badrina.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Eden%20Green%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEden%20Green%20pays%20%2414%20to%20%2425%20to%20its%20hourly%20workers%2C%20who%20do%20things%20like%20seeding%2C%20tending%20to%20plants%2C%20harvesting%2C%20and%20putting%20goods%20into%20clamshell%20packaging%2C%20he%20said.%20There%20are%20more%20than%20half%20a%20dozen%20roles%20within%20a%20greenhouse%20that%20someone%20can%20specialize%20in.%20%26quot%3BSomeone%20with%20a%20high%20school%20degree%20can%20start%20at%20the%20base%20and%20then%20work%20their%20way%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Badrina%20said.%20And%20often%2C%20in%20his%20experience%2C%20younger%20workers%20like%20the%20idea%20of%20doing%20something%20meaningful%20to%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%2C%20he%20said%2C%20helps%20Eden%20Green%20hang%20onto%20workers.%20And%20it's%20not%20just%20young%20workers%20with%20high%20school%20diplomas.%20The%20company%20employs%20people%20with%20advanced%20degrees%20in%20controlled-environment%20agriculture%2C%20horticulture%2C%20and%20plant%20biology.%20Eden%20Green's%20retention%20rate%20has%20been%20above%2080%25%20for%20the%20past%20nine%20months%2C%20the%20company%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoom%20to%20advance%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20the%20work%20itself%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0has%20kept%20Lewis%20at%20the%20company%2C%20they%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20love%20working%20with%20people%2C%20but%20plants%20have%20always%20been%20a%20passion%20of%20mine.%20So%20t