om.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fwang-xiaoshuai-china-berlin-above-the-dust-1235913938%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fwang-xiaoshuai-china-berlin-above-the-dust-1235913938%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22MGNREGA%20Led%20to%20Decline%20in%20Gender%20Wage%20Gap%2C%20Increased%20Compliance%20with%20Minimum%20Wage%20Norms%3A%20ILO%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F11115728%2Fmnrega-work.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20implementation%20and%20expansion%20of%20the%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act%20(MGNREGA)%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20decline%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap%20besides%20increasing%20compliance%20with%20minimum%20wage%20regulations%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20the%20International%20Labour%20Organisation%20(ILO)%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20are%20from%20ILO%E2%80%99s%20latest%20working%20paper%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fglobal%2Fpublications%2Fworking-papers%2FWCMS_911918%2Flang--en%2Findex.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmployment%20and%20wage%20disparities%20between%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20paper%2C%20the%20gap%20in%20rural%20wages%20between%20formal%20salaried%20workers%20and%20casual%20workers%20has%20also%20decreased%20due%20to%20the%20employment%20guarantee%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20NREGS%20was%20introduced%20and%20expanded%2C%20the%20rate%20of%20compliance%20with%20minimum%20wage%20regulations%20increased%2C%20the%20gap%20in%20rural%20wages%20between%20formal%20salaried%20workers%20and%20casual%20workers%20decreased%20and%2C%20similarly%2C%20the%20gender%20wage%20gaps%20in%20rural%20areas%20declined.%20Alongside%20other%20factors%2C%20the%20NREGS%20programme%20seems%20to%20have%20played%20an%20important%20role%20in%20these%20positive%20trends%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fmgnrega-scheme-led-to-decline-in-gender-wage-gap-in-rural-india-ilo-124021600730_1.html%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20noting%20that%20the%20scheme%20has%20been%20successful%20in%20transforming%20the%20lives%20of%20the%20rural%20populace%2C%20the%20degree%20of%20impact%20varied%20across%20the%20nation%20depending%20on%20its%20implementation%20at%20the%20field%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act%20was%20passed%20in%202005%2C%20and%20the%20demand-driven%20scheme%20guarantees%20100%20days%20of%20unskilled%20work%20per%20year%20for%20every%20rural%20household%20that%20wants%20it.%20Since%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20government%20assumed%20power%20in%202014%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fnrega-budget-allocation-2023-24%5C%22%3Ebudgetary%20allocations%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20the%20scheme%20have%20been%20reduced%20drastically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20famously%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fmnrega-monument-to-failure-of-congress-govts-modi%2Farticle10701735.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3Ecalled%20MGNREGA%20a%20%E2%80%9Cliving%20monument%20of%20Congress%20government%E2%80%99s%20failure%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20a%20speech%20in%20parliament%2C%20he%20had%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20so%20many%20years%20in%20power%2C%20all%20you%20were%20able%20to%20deliver%20is%20for%20a%20poor%20man%20to%20dig%20ditches%20a%20few%20days%20a%20month.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ILO%20working%20paper%20also%20points%20to%20negative%20trends%20in%20the%20purchasing%20power%20of%20rural%20Indian%20wages%20in%20recent%20years.%20%E2%80%9CDrawing%20on%20inflation%20data%2C%20together%20with%20the%20rural%20monthly%20wage%20index%20published%20by%20the%20Indian%20Labour%20Bureau%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%20has%20observed%20negative%20trends%20in%20the%20purchasing%20power%20of%20rural%20Indian%20wages%20in%20recent%20years.%20Thus%2C%20in%20its%20Economic%20Survey%202022-23%2C%20the%20Ministry%20highlighted%20a%20negative%20growth%20in%20real%20rural%20wages%20(that%20is%2C%20rural%20wages%20adjusted%20for%20inflation)%20due%20to%20elevated%20inflation%20between%20April%20and%20November%202022%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20paper%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20study%20uses%20household%20survey%20data%20from%2058%20countries%20around%20the%20world%20to%20compare%20the%20labour%20market%20outcomes%20of%20rural%20and%20urban%20workers%2C%20taking%20into%20account%20the%20specific%20socio-demographic%20characteristics%20of%20rural%20populations.%20It%20also%20provides%20an%20overview%20of%20the%20legal%20frameworks%20that%20can%20be%20used%20to%20address%20rural-urban%20employment%20and%20wage%20disparities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStatistical%20evidence%20from%2058%20countries%20shows%20that%20although%20people%20in%20rural%20areas%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20in%20employment%20than%20those%20in%20urban%20ones%2C%20they%20also%20tend%20to%20have%20jobs%20that%20can%20put%20them%20at%20risk%20of%20experiencing%20inadequate%20labour%20protection%20as%20well%20as%20low%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20particular%2C%20rural%20workers%20are%20paid%2C%20on%20average%2C%2024%25%20less%20than%20their%20urban%20counterparts%20on%20an%20hourly%20basis%2C%20and%20only%20half%20of%20this%20gap%20can%20be%20explained%20by%20rural-urban%20discrepancies%20in%20education%2C%20job%20experience%20and%20occupational%20category.%20Developing%20countries%20exhibit%20a%20relatively%20wider%20gap%2C%20with%20the%20unexplained%20part%20also%20being%20larger.%20Furthermore%2C%20in%20many%20countries%2C%20certain%20groups%20of%20rural%20workers%20are%20at%20greater%20disadvantage%2C%20such%20as%20women%2C%20who%2C%20on%20average%2C%20appear%20to%20earn%20less%20than%20men%20in%20rural%20areas.%20However%2C%20institutional%20and%20regulatory%20frameworks%2C%20notably%20those%20that%20set%20minimum%20wages%20or%20seek%20to%20promote%20equal%20opportunities%2C%20can%20help%20to%20reduce%20labour%20market-related%20inequalities%20across%20the%20rural-urban%20divide%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708150169000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F11115728%2Fmnrega-work.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fmgnrega-led-to-decline-in-gender-wage-gap-increased-compliance-with-minimum-wage-norms-ilo%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20latest%20working%20paper%20by%20International%20Labour%20Organisation%20has%20also%20found%20that%20the%20gap%20in%20rural%20wages%20between%20formal%20salaried%20workers%20and%20casual%20workers%20has%20also%20decreased%20due%20to%20the%20employment%20guarantee%20scheme.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fmgnrega-led-to-decline-in-gender-wage-gap-increased-compliance-with-minimum-wage-norms-ilo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shailene%20Woodley%2C%20Jack%20Whitehall%20Join%20Voice%20Cast%20of%20%E2%80%98Girl%20in%20the%20Clouds%E2%80%99%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708150140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FMixCollage-16-Feb-2024-12-13-PM-6871.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235913420%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shailene%20Woodley%20and%20Jack%20Whitehall%20have%20joined%20the%20cast%20of%20the%20animated%20feature%20%E2%80%9CGirl%20in%20the%20Clou