o%20raise%20interest%20rates%20and%20uncertainties%20surrounding%20the%20budget%2C%20coupled%20with%20a%20chronic%20shortage%20of%20skilled%20labor%2C%20further%20hamper%20Germany's%20economic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spotlight%20has%20now%20turned%20on%20India%2C%20which%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20beacon%20of%20opportunity%20for%20investors.%20Projections%20from%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20suggest%20that%20India%20is%20poised%20to%20overtake%20both%20Japan%20and%20Germany%20in%20terms%20of%20economic%20output%2C%20with%20estimates%20placing%20the%20shift%20in%202026%20and%202027%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20remains%20the%20fastest-growing%20large%20economy%20and%20its%20growth%20is%20projected%20to%20reach%206.2%20per%20cent%20in%202024%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Economic%20Situation%20and%20Prospects%202024%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20currently%20the%20world's%20fifth-largest%20economy%2C%20placed%20behind%20the%20US%2C%20China%2C%20Japan%20and%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gross%20Domestic%20Product%20(GDP)%20of%20the%20US%20in%202023%20was%20%2427.94%20trillion%2C%20while%20China's%20was%20%2417.5%20trillion.%20India's%20GDP%20is%20about%20%243.7%20trillion%20but%20growing%20at%20a%20sizzling%20rate%20of%20around%207%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20benefiting%20from%20growing%20interest%20from%20multinationals%2C%20which%20see%20the%20country%20as%20a%20key%20alternative%20manufacturing%20base%20in%20the%20context%20of%20developed%20economies'%20supply%20chain%20diversification%20strategies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gap%20between%20developed%20countries%20and%20emerging%20nations%20is%20shrinking%2C%20with%20India%20now%20all%20set%20to%20capitalise%20on%20the%20opportunity%20to%20become%20a%20significant%20player%20in%20the%20global%20economic%20landscape.%20The%20shifting%20dynamics%20present%20a%20moment%20for%20India%20to%20assert%20its%20influence%20and%20contribute%20substantia