sted%20as%20accidental%20and%20suicides.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20a%20look%20at%20some%20of%20the%20high-profile%20deaths%20involving%20those%20who%20have%20criticised%20the%20Russian%20leader%20over%20the%20years%20-%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EYevgeny%20Prigozhin%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20head%20of%20the%20Wagner%20paramilitary%20group%20was%20once%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20most%20powerful%20oligarchs%20and%20a%20member%20of%20Mr%20Putin's%20trusted%20inner%20circle.%20He%20died%20in%202023%20at%20the%20age%20of%2062%20when%20the%20plane%20he%20was%20flying%20in%20exploded%20midair.%20Notably%2C%20the%20unexplained%20blast%20came%20two%20months%20after%20Mr%20Prigozhin%20led%20a%20failed%20mutiny%20against%20Russia's%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20over%20a%20disagreement%20with%20the%20direction%20of%20Moscow's%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20led%20a%20dramatic%20%26quot%3Bmarch%20for%20justice%26quot%3B%20where%20armed%20men%20were%20seen%20heading%20towards%20the%20Russian%20capital%20in%20June%202023.%20As%20Mr%20Putin%20remained%20silent%2C%20the%20mutiny%20was%20suddenly%20aborted.%20Mr%20Prigozhin%20ordered%20his%20troops%20to%20lay%20down%20their%20arms%2C%20before%20they%20were%20relocated%20to%20Belarus%20under%20a%20deal%20brokered%20by%20that%20country's%20Russia-allied%20president%2C%20Alexander%20Lukashenko.%20But%20two%20months%20later%2C%20Mr%20Prigozhin%20plummeted%20from%20the%20sky%20when%20the%20jet%20he%20was%20flying%20on%20from%20Moscow%20to%20St%20Petersburg%20apparently%20exploded.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKremlin%20critics%20and%20Western%20countries%20suggested%20foul%20play.%20However%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20denied%20any%20involvement%20in%20the%20downing%20of%20the%20aircraft.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBoris%20Nemtsov%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoris%20Nemtsov%2C%20a%20vocal%20Kremlin%20critic%20who%20was%20a%20deputy%20prime%20minister%20in%20the%20late%201990s%20under%20President%20Boris%20Yeltsin%2C%20was%20gunned%20down%20in%20February%202015%20on%20a%20bridge%20close%20to%20the%20Kremlin%20in%20Moscow.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F02%2F16%2Feurope%2Fputin-critics-dead-alexey-navalny-intl-cmd%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20had%20been%20arrested%20several%20times%20for%20speaking%20against%20Mr%20Putin's%20government.%20When%20he%20was%20killed%2C%20he%20was%20helping%20to%20set%20up%20a%20rally%20against%20the%20Russian%20military%20incursion%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20began%20in%202014%20with%20the%20annexation%20of%20Crimea%20and%20the%20support%20of%20supposed%20separatists%20in%20the%20Donbas%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBoris%20Berezovsky%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoris%20Berezovsky%20was%20once%20a%20powerful%20Russian%20businessman%20who%20fell%20out%20with%20the%20Kremlin%20and%20fled%20to%20England.%20He%20had%20accumulated%20his%20wealth%20following%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%20A%20large%20chunk%20of%20his%20fortune%20came%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20luxury%20cars.%20But%20his%20wealth%20and%20political%20influence%20skyrocketed%20when%20he%20bought%20into%20Russian%20media.%20He%20relocated%20to%20Britain%20after%20losing%20favour%20with%20Mr%20Putin's%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20Mr%20Berezovsky%20was%20found%20dead%20on%20the%20bathroom%20floor%20of%20his%20UK%20home%20with%20a%20noose%20around%20his%20neck.%20British%20police%20said%20at%20the%20time%20that%20there%20were%20no%20signs%20of%20struggle%20and%20suggested%20that%20he%20had%20taken%20his%20own%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlexander%20Litvinenko%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Litvinenko%20was%20a%20former%20Russian%20spy%20turned%20Kremlin%20critic.%20A%20British%20inquiry%20determined%20Alexander%20Litvinenko%20had%20been%20poisoned%20at%20a%20London%20hotel%20bar%20in%202006%20by%20two%20Russian%20agents%20who%20spiked%20his%20green%20tea%20with%20the%20highly%20radioactive%20polonium-210%2C%20%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%20Mr%20Litvinenko%20also%20always%20asserted%20that%20Mr%20Putin%20and%20the%20Kremlin%20were%20responsible%20for%20what%20had%20happened%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Kremlin%20has%20always%20denied%20the%20accusation%20and%20has%20refused%20to%20extradite%20the%20two%20agents%20accused%20of%20the%20poisoning%20to%20Britain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERavil%20Maganov%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERavil%20Maganov%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20board%20of%20Russia's%20second%20largest%20oil%20producer%20Lukoil%2C%20died%20six%20months%20after%20he%20openly%20criticised%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%20He%20died%20after%20falling%20out%20of%20the%20window%20of%20a%20Moscow%20hospital.%20Russian%20state%20news%20agency%20%3Cem%3ETass%20%3C%2Fem%3Eclaimed%20his%20death%20was%20a%20suicide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnna%20Politkovskaya%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Politkovskaya%20was%20a%20vocal%20critic%20of%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Chechnya.%20She%20was%20gunned%20down%20in%20the%20entrance%20of%20her%20Moscow%20apartment%20in%20October%202006.%20Her%20death%20garnered%20international%20attention%20and%20it%20wasn't%20until%20June%202014%20that%20five%20men%20were%20sentenced%20for%20the%20killing%2C%20but%20it%20remains%20unclear%20who%20ordered%20the%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20shortly%20after%20her%20death%2C%20Mr%20Putin%20denied%20any%20Kremlin%20involvement%20in%20her%20killing%2C%20saying%20that%20Ms%20Politkovskaya's%20%26quot%3Bdeath%20in%20itself%20is%20more%20damaging%20to%20the%20current%20authorities%20both%20in%20Russia%20and%20the%20Chechen%20Republic%20...%20than%20her%20activities%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESergei%20Magnitsky%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESergei%20Magnitsky%2C%20a%20Russian%20tax%20adviser%20who%20exposed%20corruption%2C%20was%20detained%20without%20a%20trial%20and%20died%20in%20prison%20just%20seven%20days%20before%20he%20was%20set%20to%20be%20released.%20He%20was%20arrested%20in%202008%20and%20died%20on%2016%20November%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlexander%20Perepilichnyy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Perepilichnyy%20was%20a%20financier%20who%20became%20a%20whistleblower%20in%202010%20when%20he%20handed%20over%20files%20to%20Swiss%20officials%20showing%20details%20of%20the%20%24230%20million%20theft%20of%20funds%20from%20the%20Russian%20treasury.%20He%20died%20during%20a%20jog%20close%20to%20London%20in%202012%20after%20leaving%20Russia%20in%202009.%20While%20he%20was%20found%20to%20probably%20have%20died%20of%20natural%20causes%2C%20there%20are%20allegations%20that%20he%20was%20poisoned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20people%20mentioned%20above%2C%20at%20least%2013%20high-profile%20Russian%20businessmen%20have%20reportedly%20died%20by%20suicide%20or%20in%20mysterious%20circumstances%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20as%20per%20%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708147800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fab6qiv58_putin-reuters_625x300_06_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Falexei-navalny-to-yevgeny-prigozhin-heres-a-list-of-putin-critics-who-died-mysteriously-5074087%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Alexei%20Navalny's%20death%20is%20only%20the%20most%20recent%20of%20a%20long%20line%20of%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20critics%20who%20have%20been%20jailed%2C%20silenced%20or%20met%20brutal%20ends%20over%20the%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Falexei-navalny-to-yevgeny-prigozhin-heres-a-list-of-putin-critics-who-died-mysteriously-5074087%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Falexei-navalny-to-yevgeny-prigozhin-heres-a-list-of-putin-critics-who-died-mysteriously-5074087%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Falexei-navalny-to-yevgeny-prigozhin-heres-a-list-of-putin-critics-who-died-mysteriously-5074087%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Alexei%20Navalny's%20Death%20Spells%20the%20End%20of%20Politics%20in%20Russia%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17104400%2FScreenshot-2024-02-17-at-10.42.2.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EReports%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2Ffeb%2F16%2Frussian-activist-and-putin-critic-alexei-navalny-dies-in-prison%5C%22%3Eof%20the%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20most%20famous%20opposition%20leader%2C%20Alexei%20Navalny%2C%20in%20an%20Arctic%20prison%20camp%20are%20shocking%2C%20but%20not%20entirely%20unexpected.%20It%20draws%20a%20line%20under%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20political%20development%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%20by%20highlighting%20that%20a%20challenge%20from%20within%20is%20no%20longer%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%20was%20the%20last%20public%20politician%20to%20pose%20a%20real%20challenge%20to%20the%20Kremlin%2C%20but%20his%20attempt%20to%20overthrow%20the%20regime%20failed%20long%20before%20what%20appears%20to%20be%20his%20untimely%20death%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20unrealistic%20calculations%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20his%20return%20to%20Russia%20in%202021%20led%20to%20the%20dismantling%20of%20the%20remnants%20of%20any%20organised%20opposition%20that%20was%20not%20sanctioned%20%E2%80%93%20and%20controlled%20%E2%80%93%20by%20the%20Russian%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%20ended%20up%20in%20prison%2C%20his%20supporters%20arrested%20or%20fled%20abroad.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20when%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20came%2C%20there%20were%20very%20few%20street%20protests%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EActive%20in%20Russian%20politics%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FInternational%2FwireStory%2Fprotests-poisoning-prison-life-russian-opposition-leader-alexei-107288919%23%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2020%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20main%20focus%20was%20identifying%20and%20rooting%20out%20state%20corruption%2C%20an%20issue%20with%20almost%20limitless%20material%20in%20modern%20Russia.%20He%20embraced%20new%20methods%20of%20bringing%20his%20investigations%20to%20as%20wide%20an%20audience%20as%20he%20could%2C%20notably%20the%20internet%2C%20particularly%20via%20his%20YouTube%20channel.%20Some%20of%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F1202972%2Fmost-popular-videos-by-alexei-navalny%2F%5C%22%3Emost%20popular%20clips%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20corruption%20investigations%20and%20blogging%20were%20not%20enough%20to%20really%20challenge%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20status%20quo%20in%20Russian%20politics.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20Navalny%20increasingly%20turned%20to%20the%20direct%20action%20of%20mass%20street%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20big%20break%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2011%2Fdec%2F10%2Frussia-protests-election-vladimir-putin%5C%22%3Ecame%20in%202011%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20allegations%20of%20widespread%20fraud%20in%20the%20December%202011%20Duma%20elections%2C%20coupled%20with%20the%20announcement%20of%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20return%20to%20the%20presidency%20the%20previous%20September%2C%20brought%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20protesters%20on%20to%20the%20streets%20of%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20protests%20were%20not%20organised%20by%20Navalny%2C%20his%20charisma%20and%20more%20radical%20rhetoric%20made%20him%20the%20most%20prominent%20face%20of%20the%20protests%2C%20overshadowing%20more%20established%20opposition%20leaders%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2015%2Fmar%2F01%2Fboris-nemtsov%5C%22%3EBoris%20Nemtsov%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20the%20mass%20protests%20of%202011-12%20failed%20to%20prevent%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20re-election%20in%20March%202012%2C%20and%20eventually%20fizzled%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20protests%20prompted%20the%20Kremlin%20to%20change%20tack%20and%20experiment%20with%20allowing%20the%20opposition%20to%20stand%20in%20elections.%20Navalny%20was%20the%20main%20beneficiary%2C%20being%20registered%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2013%2Fsep%2F09%2Falexei-navalny-recount-moscow-election%5C%22%3EMoscow%20mayoral%20elections%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202013.%20This%20was%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20only%20real%20chance%20of%20winning%20power%20in%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20tightly%20controlled%20electoral%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20campaigned%20enthusiastically%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2013%2Fsep%2F09%2Falexei-navalny-recount-moscow-election%5C%22%3Ewon%20a%20respectable%2027%25%20of%20the%20vote%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20it%20also%20showed%20the%20limits%20of%20his%20appeal.%20Moscow%20was%20at%20the%20time%20one%20of%20the%20most%20opposition-leaning%20cities%20in%20Russia%2C%20one%20of%20the%20few%20regions%20where%20Putin%20got%20less%20than%2050%25%20in%20the%202012%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20opposition%20could%20really%20challenge%20the%20Kremlin%2C%20it%20was%20in%20Moscow.%20But%20turnout%20was%20extremely%20low%20at%2032%25%2C%20and%20the%20incumbent%20mayor%2C%20Sergey%20Sobyanin%2C%20won%20the%2051%25%20he%20needed%20to%20avoid%20a%20run-off%20with%20Navalny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20indicative%20of%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20problem%3A%20reliance%20on%20restriction%20to%20a%20committed%20core%20of%20supporters%20whose%20passion%20for%20change%20didn%E2%80%99t%20spill%20over%20into%20the%20general%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELast%20roll%20of%20the%20dice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElections%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20Russia%20are%20a%20foregone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fputin-is-sure-to-win-so-whats-the-point-of-elections-in-russia-93170%5C%22%3Econclusion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20they%20are%20also%20a%20potential%20vulnerability%20for%20the%20Kremlin.%20There%20is%20a%20fine%20balance%20that%20the%20Kremlin%20has%20to%20strike%20between%20control%20of%20elections%20and%20their%20legitimacy.%20Too%20much%20control%2C%20or%20outright%20fraud%2C%20and%20the%20legitimising%20value%20of%20the%20elections%20is%20reduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20lead%20to%20potentially%20destabilising%20results%2C%20as%20the%20mass%20protests%20in%20Moscow%20in%202011%20or%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2021%2F01%2F13%2Fbelarus-unprecedented-crackdown%5C%22%3Eprotests%20in%20Belarus%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%2C%20and%20as%20happened%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2004%2Fnov%2F26%2Fukraine.usa%5C%22%3E2004%20Ukrainian%20elections%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20led%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlanticcouncil.org%2Fblogs%2Fukrainealert%2Fhow-ukraines-orange-revolution-shaped-twenty-first-century-geopolitics%2F%5C%22%3Efirst%20Orange%20Revolution%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%20understood%20this%20well%2C%20and%20made%20participation%20in%20the%202018%20presidential%20election%20his%20main%20goal.%20His%20strategy%20was%20to%20cause%20enough%20trouble%20for%20the%20authorities%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20vote%2C%20particularly%20through%20various%20street%20demonstrations%2C%20to%20force%20the%20authorities%20to%20allow%20him%20to%20stand%20as%20an%20official%20candidate%20in%20these%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%20end%2C%20he%20set%20up%20a%20regional%20network%20of%20Navalny%20HQs%20that%20ran%20in%20parallel%20with%20his%20main%20anti-corruption%20organisation%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rferl.org%2Fa%2Frussia-navalny-corruption-foundation%2F31938527.html%5C%22%3EFBK%20(the%20Anti-Corruption%20Foundation)%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20gave%20Navalny%20a%20potential%20nationwide%20reach%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20old%20Moscow-centred%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20strategy%20didn%E2%80%99t%20produce%20the%20desired%20result%20of%20getting%20Navalny%20on%20to%20the%20ballot.%20But%20it%20seemed%20to%20rattle%20the%20authorities%20enough%20to%20want%20to%20take%20care%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9CNavalny%20problem%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoison%20and%20imprisonment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202020%2C%20Navalny%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Falexei-navalny-suspected-poisoning-why-opposition-figure-stands-out-in-russian-politics-144836%5C%22%3Efell%20ill%20on%20a%20flight%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%2C%20according%20to%20the%20German%20doctors%20who%20treated%20him%2C%20escaped%20near-certain%20death%20from%20a%20Novichok%20weapons-grade%20chemical%20agent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20returned%20from%20Germany%20in%20January%202021%20and%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Falexei-navalny-novichok-didnt-stop-russian-opposition-leader-but-a-prison-sentence-might-153480%5C%22%3Eimmediately%20arrested%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20landing%20in%20Moscow.%20The%20mass%20protests%20that%20followed%20were%20unusual%20for%20their%20regional%20scale%2C%20but%20not%20enough%20to%20really%20challenge%20the%20Kremlin.%20Instead%2C%20the%20authorities%20banned%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20organisations%20in%20Russia%20and%20either%20arrested%20or%20forced%20those%20who%20worked%20for%20them%20to%20flee%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%E2%80%99s%20fate%20became%20the%20main%20point%20of%20contention%20for%20Moscow%20in%20its%20dealings%20with%20western%20governments%20and%20media.%20Navalny%20was%20the%20obligatory%20subject%20of%20high-level%20contacts%20with%20the%20Russian%20authorities%2C%20with%20Joe%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20national%20security%20adviser%20Jake%20Sullivan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-56794744%5C%22%3Ewarning%20that%20Russia%20would%20suffer%20consequences%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20Navalny%20died%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20all%20this%20paled%20into%20insignificance%20after%20the%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20at%20the%20end%20of%20February%202022.%20Overnight%2C%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20fate%20seemed%20diminished%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20Europe%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20war%20since%201945.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%E2%80%99s%20own%20agenda%20of%20generating%20enough%20domestic%20protest%20to%20topple%20the%20regime%20became%20obsolete%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fnews%2F2022%2F03%2Frussia-kremlins-ruthless-crackdown-stifles-independent-journalism-and-anti-war-movement%2F%5C%22%3Enew%20anti-opposition%20laws%20were%20enforced%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20most%20of%20his%20most%20ardent%20supporters%20fled%20the%20country.%20Navalny%20tried%20to%20stay%20relevant%20by%20promoting%20his%20views%20from%20prison%2C%20including%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F4fishgreenberg.medium.com%2Falexey-navalny-on-the-anniversary-of-the-russian-invasion-of-ukraine-2aa18f5602c4%5C%22%3Ecall%20to%20end%20the%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20handing%20over%20all%20Ukrainian%20territory%2C%20including%20Crimea%2C%20and%20paying%20reparations%20to%20Ukraine.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20clear%20that%20he%20gained%20any%20supporters%20in%20Russia%2C%20but%20he%20certainly%20appealed%20to%20those%20in%20exile%20and%20to%20western%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20West%20and%20its%20allies%20imposing%20an%20unprecedented%20level%20of%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%20and%20providing%20Ukraine%20with%20the%20military%20support%20to%20defeat%20Putin%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20literally%20nothing%20else%20the%20west%20can%20do%20to%20punish%20Russia%20over%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20fate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20rest%20is%20dictatorship%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlexei%20Navalny%20was%20clearly%20a%20very%20brave%20and%20charismatic%20politician%20who%20posed%20the%20most%20significant%20domestic%20challenge%20to%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20regime%20in%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%20He%20never%20really%20came%20close%20to%20toppling%20Putin%2C%20and%20perhaps%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Falexei-navalny-novichok-didnt-stop-russian-opposition-leader-but-a-prison-sentence-might-153480%5C%22%3Eoverestimated%20his%20level%20of%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20news%20of%20his%20untimely%20death%20in%20prison%2C%20the%20question%20remains%20whether%20he%20could%20have%20done%20more%20from%20exile%20in%20the%20west.%20He%20would%20have%20joined%20a%20long%20list%20of%20Russian%20opposition%20leaders%2C%20from%20former%20oligarch%20Mikhail%20Khodorkovsky%20to%20chess%20champion%20Garry%20Kasparov%2C%20who%20have%20virtually%20no%20influence%20on%20what%20happens%20in%20Russia.%20But%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20go%20down%20that%20road%2C%20and%20his%20belief%20in%20his%20own%20importance%2C%20is%20precisely%20what%20has%20made%20him%20stand%20out%20in%20Russian%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20death%20draws%20a%20line%20under%20the%20era%20when%20politics%20was%20politics%20in%20Russia.%20Today%20there%20is%20only%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20own%20personal%20authoritarianism.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F223766%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAlexander%20Titov%2C%20Lecturer%20in%20Modern%20European%20History%2C%20Queen%E2%80%99s%20University%20Belfast.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Falexei-navalny-reported-death-of-putins-most-prominent-opponent-spells-the-end-of-politics-in-russia-223766%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708147017000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17104400%2FScreenshot-2024-02-17-at-10.42.2.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Falexei-navalnys-death-spells-the-end-of-politics-in-russia%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Today%20there%20is%20only%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20own%20personal%20authoritarianism.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Falexei-navalnys-death-spells-the-end-of-politics-in-russia%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fire%20in%20New%20Jersey%20building%20displaces%20dozens%2C%20including%20Indian%20students%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708146937000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107770527%2Cimgsize-820538.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fdozen-indian-students-and-prefessionals-displaced-in-new-jerseys-fire-incident%2Farticleshow%2F107770398.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107770398.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EA%20fire%20in%20a%20Jersey%20City%20residential%20building%20displaced%20several%20Indian%20students%20and%20professionals%2C%20confirmed%20safe%20by%20the%20Consulate%20General%20of%20India%20in%20New%20York.%20The%20Consulat